 ## Version-by-Version Build Map 
 
 ## v1.1 — Core CRM Vertical Slice 
 ### Goal 
 Ship production-grade Organizations + Opportunities with strong domain boundaries. 
 
 ### Deliverables 
 - Organizations domain module (CRUD + ownership + status). 
 - Opportunities domain module (create/list/detail + organization linkage). 
 - Workflow transition guardrails and stage history. 
 
 ### Acceptance 
 - Parity with current baseline business flow. 
 - End-to-end tests for core lead-to-opportunity journey. 
 - P95 latency and error budgets defined and passing. 
 
 ## v1.2 — Workflow Integrity & Timeline 
 ### Goal 
 Make work state transitions auditable, queryable, and operationally safe. 
 
 ### Deliverables 
 - Unified activities timeline. 
 - Tasking/follow-up model. 
 - Workflow rules with explicit state machine constraints. 
 
 ### Acceptance 
 - Immutable transition history. 
 - No invalid state transitions possible via API. 
 - Audit trail available per record. 
 
 ## v1.3 — Invoicing & Async Operations 
 ### Goal 
 Introduce financial workflows without blocking request-response paths. 
 
 ### Deliverables 
 - Invoice lifecycle (draft/finalized/cancelled). 
 - PDF generation and delivery via queue workers. 
 - Retry + dead-letter strategy. 
 
 ### Acceptance 
 - Zero synchronous long-running invoice processing in API requests. 
 - Recoverable failure paths with operational runbooks. 
 
 ## v1.4 — Reporting Reliability Layer 
 ### Goal 
 Stabilize KPIs and dashboards with read-model architecture. 
 
 ### Deliverables 
 - Materialized/read models for dashboard metrics. 
 - Metric dictionary with ownership and formulas. 
 - Scheduled refresh and backfill jobs. 
 
 ### Acceptance 
 - KPI definitions consistent across UI and exports. 
 - Reporting endpoints meet performance SLOs at target scale. 
 
 ## v1.5 — Integrations & Automation at Scale 
 ### Goal 
 Enable controlled external interoperability and automation. 
 
 ### Deliverables 
 - Outbox/event delivery framework. 
 - Webhook management (retry, signature verification, replay protection). 
 - Automation rules engine v1 (reminders/escalations). 
 
 ### Acceptance 
 - At-least-once external delivery with dedupe protections. 
 - Operational visibility for integration failures. 
 
 ## v2.0 — Cutover + Optimization 
 ### Goal 
 Complete migration from legacy path and optimize for scale. 
 
 ### Deliverables 
 - Parallel run validation. 
 - Production cutover and rollback drill completion. 
 - Post-cutover performance tuning and cost controls. 
 
 ### Acceptance 
 - Cutover executed with rollback confidence. 
 - SLOs sustained for agreed stabilization window. 
 
